net.enilink.commons.iterator

Class UniqueExtendedIterator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.enilink.commons.iterator.NiceIterator<T>
      • net.enilink.commons.iterator.WrappedIterator<T>
        • net.enilink.commons.iterator.UniqueExtendedIterator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Iterable<T>, Iterator<T>, IExtendedIterator<T>

    public class UniqueExtendedIterator<T>
extends WrappedIterator<T>
    A variant on the closable/extended iterator that filters out duplicate values. There is one complication that the value which filtering is done on might not be the actual value to be returned by the iterator.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.16 $ on $Date: 2008/01/02 12:07:36 $
    Author:
    Dave Reynolds

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static <T> IExtendedIterator<T> create(Iterator<T> it)
        Factory method for generating an iterator that is guaranteed only to return one instance of every result from the wrapped iterator it.
        Parameters:
        it - An iterator to wrap
        Returns:
        A iterator that returns the elements of the wrapped iterator exactly once. If it is already a unique extended iteator, it is not further wrapped.

      • nextIfNew

        protected T nextIfNew()
        Fetch the next object to be returned, only if not already seen. Subclasses which need to filter on different objects than the return values should override this method.
        Returns:
        the object to be returned or null if the object has been filtered.
